Today Kosovo celebrated 11 years of independence. Before the parade, I had lunch at a cafe in Pristina.

When I asked for the check the waiter simply smiled and said, "It's on the house."

I asked why.

"Your country saved mine," he said. "The least I can do is buy you lunch."
